cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SI 

The paper focuses on deep learning and autoencoders, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also specifically discusses convolutional autoencoders, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper proposes a new type of autoencoder that can be interpreted as a learned wavelet shrinkage system, which relates to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also includes denoising experiments, which relate to the sub-category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the interpretability of deep learning models, which is a topic commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
